The paper deals with the problem of computing cohesive subgraphs in a graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The focus of the paper is on the k densest subgraphs problem, which is a variant of the cohesive subgraphs problem and involves finding multiple subgraphs rather than just one. This problem is closely related to graph algorithms and computational complexity (cs.DS), as well as computational geometry and topology (cs.CC) due to the use of geometric concepts such as density. The paper also involves analyzing the theoretical complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
